  "prompt": "How do I find a UI designer job in Maryland?",
  "response": "To find a UI designer job in Maryland, you can try the following strategies:\n\n1. Online Job Platforms\n- LinkedIn Jobs\n- Indeed\n- Glassdoor\n- ZipRecruiter\n- Monster\n- Design-specific job boards like Behance and Dribbble\n\n2. Local Job Search Resources\n- Maryland Job Source\n- Maryland Department of Labor website\n- Local tech job boards\n- University career centers (University of Maryland, Johns Hopkins)\n\n3. Networking\n- Attend tech and design meetups in Baltimore and Washington D.C.\n- Join professional design groups on LinkedIn\n- Connect with local design professionals\n- Participate in design conferences and events\n\n4. Company Websites\n- Check career pages of tech companies in Maryland\n- Look for design positions at:\n  - Baltimore tech companies\n  - Government agencies\n  - Design agencies\n  - Software companies\n\n5. Recruitment Agencies\n- Specialized design and tech recruitment firms\n- Robert Half Technology\n- Creative Circle\n- TEKsystems\n\n6. Freelance Platforms\n- Upwork\n- Toptal\n- Freelancer.com\n\n7. Professional Associations\n- AIGA Maryland\n- UX/UI design groups\n- Professional networking events\n\nApply broadly and tailor your portfolio to showcase relevant skills.",
